com.inqwell.any.client.swing

Class JTable.MultiListSelectionModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inqwell.any.client.swing.JTable.MultiListSelectionModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventListener, ListSelectionListener, ListSelectionModel
    Enclosing class:
    JTable

    public class JTable.MultiListSelectionModel
extends Object
implements ListSelectionModel, ListSelectionListener
    Handle varying selection models without the JTable having to know which one is in effect at any given time. This means that any event listeners setup on JTable.getSelectionModel() will not be lost when the selection model changes.

    Handles changes between flat and tree table modes without the JTable's selection model actually changing.
